{{Infobox language |name=Naka |altname=Kresh-Boro |nativename=''Gbaya'' |states=[[South Sudan]] |speakers=unknown: 16,000 all Kresh languages apart from Furu |date=2013 |ref=e18<!--2013 figure from Ethnologue 18 is a new figure that happens to be the same as the one from the 1980s--> |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Central Sudanic languages|Central Sudanic]] |fam3=Western |fam4=[[Kresh languages]] |iso3=krs |iso3comment=(KreshâGbayaâWoroâDongo) |glotto=naka1261 |glottorefname=Naka }}
'''Naka''', also known as '''Kresh-Boro''', is a [[Central Sudanic language]] of [[South Sudan]]. It is the natively most widely spoken of the [[Kresh languages]], and the second most widely understood after [[Kresh-Ndogo]].
